content:
In CRM Analytics, if a text column contains dates in different formats, use the Format Dates recipe transformation in a Data Prep recipe to standardize the format for all dates in the column. A consistent format enables you to correctly filter and group records by date, including filtering by date component, such as month.

To create this transformation:

* Select the text (dimension) column that contains dates in the Preview tab.
* Click the Format Dates button.
* Enter the original date formats in the selected column.
* Select the desired date format.
* To convert a text (dimension) column with dates to a Date column type, select Convert column type to Date.
* Set the label under Column Label and click Apply.

When you run the recipe, the transformation replaces the dates in the existing column with dates in the specified format. If the date's original format can't be determined or the date doesnâ€™t have a value for a date component, the transformation replaces the date with null.

Required user permissions: Edit Analytics Dataflows OR Edit Dataset Recipes
title: Standardizing Date Formats in CRM Analytics
